## Proposed Changes

### Database Models

#### [NEW] `src/models/StudentProfile.ts`
Extended student data captured at registration (beyond the existing [User](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/User.ts#3-16) model):
- `userId` → ref to [User](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/User.ts#3-16)
- `gender`, `dateOfBirth`, `mobileNumber`
- `highestQualification`, `yearOfPassing`, `englishComfortLevel`
- `emailVerified: boolean`

#### [NEW] `src/models/EmailOTP.ts`
For email OTP verification flow:
- `email`, `hashedOTP` (bcrypt hashed)
- `expiresAt` (5 min TTL)
- `attempts` (max 3)
- `lastSentAt` (for rate limiting resend)
- `verified: boolean`
- TTL index on `expiresAt` for auto-cleanup

#### [NEW] `src/models/Resume.ts`
Single document per student (upsert on save):
- `userId` → ref to [User](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/User.ts#3-16)
- `careerObjective: string`
- `address: { state, district, customText }`
- `skills: string[]`
- `languages: string[]`
- `education: [{ qualification, institution, yearOfPassing, percentage }]`
- `internship: { hasInternship, hospitalName, duration, role }`
- `experience: { hasFresher, jobRole, organization, duration, responsibilities[] }`

---

### Backend APIs

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts` — `POST`
Self-registration for new students:
- Validates uniqueness of email/username
- Hashes password with bcrypt
- Creates [User](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/User.ts#3-16) (role=student, status=active) + `StudentProfile`
- Returns success (email OTP send is triggered next)

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/auth/send-otp/route.ts` — `POST`
- Generates 6-digit OTP
- Hashes with bcrypt, upserts `EmailOTP` record
- Sends email via **Hostinger SMTP** (`nodemailer`) with branded template
- Rate limiting: rejects resend if `lastSentAt` < 60 seconds ago

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/auth/verify-otp/route.ts` — `POST`
- Finds OTP record by email
- Rejects if expired, already verified, or attempts ≥ 3
- Compares plain OTP vs hashed with `bcrypt.compare`
- On success: marks `emailVerified=true` in `StudentProfile`

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/auth/resend-otp/route.ts` — `POST`
- Same as send-otp but increments resend counter with 60s rate limit

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/student/resume/route.ts` — [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/documents/requirements/%5Bid%5D/route.ts#9-59) + `POST`
- [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/documents/requirements/%5Bid%5D/route.ts#9-59): Returns current student's resume data
- `POST`: Upsert resume (create or update). Protected by session auth.

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/student/resume/pdf/route.ts` — [GET](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/documents/requirements/%5Bid%5D/route.ts#9-59)
- Retrieves student's resume data
- Renders an HTML template of the resume (A4 layout)
- Returns it as a streamed HTML response for client-side PDF generation

---

### Frontend Pages & Components

#### [NEW] `src/app/(public)/register/page.tsx`
Multi-step registration form — 4 steps:
1. **Basic Details** — Full Name, Gender, DOB, Mobile, Email
2. **Academic Details** — Qualification dropdown, Year of Passing, English Comfort Level (with helper text accordion)
3. **Email OTP** — 6 input boxes, countdown timer (5 min), resend link
4. **Success screen** — Congratulations + Go to Dashboard

Built as a client component with `useState` step progression.

#### [MODIFY] [src/app/(student)/student/page.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28student%29/student/page.tsx)
Add new quick-action cards to student dashboard:
- **My Profile** — edit registration details
- **Resume Builder** — create/edit resume
- **Download Resume** — direct PDF download

#### [NEW] `src/app/(student)/student/resume/page.tsx`
Guided Resume Builder — accordion-style sections following the Stitch design:
- Personal Info (auto-filled, read-only)
- Career Objective (dropdown + custom)
- Education (auto-filled + add more)
- Skills (multi-select chip buttons)
- Training / Internship (Yes/No toggle)
- Work Experience (Fresher / Yes toggle)
- Languages Known (multi-select chips)

#### [NEW] `src/app/(student)/student/resume/preview/page.tsx`
A4 Resume Preview page — renders resume HTML from stored data, matching the Stitch design. Includes a "⬇ Download as PDF" button using `react-to-pdf` or `html2pdf.js`.

---

### Libraries to Install
```bash
npm install nodemailer @types/nodemailer html2pdf.js
```

> [!NOTE]
> `html2pdf.js` runs client-side only. It will be dynamically imported to avoid SSR issues.

